# ContentItemMenu Component Rule

The [ContentItemMenu.vue](mdc:src/components/menus/ContentItemMenu/ContentItemMenu.vue) component follows shadcn-vue conventions:

- It is a single file component (SFC) in the `src/components/menus/ContentItemMenu` directory.
- Uses Radix Vue primitives (e.g., PopoverRoot, PopoverTrigger, PopoverContent) for menu logic and accessibility.
- Uses Tailwind CSS for styling and utility classes.
- Menu actions are handled via composables for separation of concerns.
- Follows the pattern of exposing props for control (e.g., `:open`, `@update:open`).

For menu and popover best practices, see the [shadcn-vue Dropdown Menu documentation](mdc:https:/www.shadcn-vue.com/docs/components/dropdown-menu).



